<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; GRANTS: WRITERS, FILMMAKERS GET $54,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Community Foundation has awarded eight Westside writers, 
filmmakers and arts organizations more than $54,000 in grants and fellowships 
through its annual Arts Funding Program and Brody Arts Fund Awards. 
</P>
<P>
 The recipients of the literary fellowships include Palms resident F. Lawrence 
Fargo Jr. and writers Russell C. Leong of Westwood and Mark Perlstein of West 
Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Grants awarded by the California Community Foundation Arts Funding Program 
include $18,000 for Cornerstone Theatre Project of Santa Monica for its work 
with the Watts Community Bridge Project and $12,000 to the Santa Monica Museum 
of Art for its work in Art Partners, an arts education project helping 
disadvantaged Los Angeles County high school students. 
</P>
<P>
 Independent Feature Project/West of Santa Monica received $11,000 for "Involve 
Productions," a project designed to give hands-on instruction in independent 
film production. Other recipients included the Los Angeles Baroque Orchestra of 
Marina del Rey and Imagination Workshop, a Westwood theater group. 
