<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; FILM: 5 ACTORS, DIRECTORS TO BE HONORED AT FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 1994 American Film Institute's International Film Festival opens today in 
Santa Monica at Laemmle's Monica Theatres. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival, which runs through July 7, will coincide with the World Cup 
USA's cultural showcase, Arts94.Five actors and directors will be honored in 
nightly tributes that will include a showing of the artist's works and a 
question and answer session with the honoree. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday, the institute will honor Dennis Hopper, a writer, director and 
actor who starred in "Easy Rider" and "Blue Velvet." In his question and answer 
period, he will be joined by actor Sean Penn. 
</P>
<P>
 Academy Award winner Holly Hunter will be on hand Sunday for a tribute session 
moderated by Jean Firstenberg, director of the institute. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival is open to the public with movie showings from 1:20 to 9 p.m. at 
the Laemmle Theatres, 1332 2nd St., Santa Monica. Admission for all movies and 
tributes is $7.50. Information: Theatix, (213) 466-1767. 
