<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOPICS; ENVIRONMENT; ANTI-MOSQUITO TIPS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Gabriel Valley Mosquito Abatement District is offering tips for 
residents with mosquito problems during breeding season, which starts with warm 
weather and extends to September. 
</P>
<P>
 Some mosquitoes transmit serious diseases. Female mosquitoes can transmit the 
St. Louis encephalitis virus, which can cause inflammation of the brain and 
spinal cord. Between 1984 and 1993, Los Angeles County had 25 reported cases of 
the virus, including one death. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials encourage residents to eliminate breeding sources such as 
standing water in buckets, planters, old tires, cans, jars and other 
containers. For residents who have ponds, the district will provide free fish 
that eat developing mosquito larvae. Information: (818) 814-9466. 
</P>
</TEXT>
