<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: REGION; UCLA SEEKS VOLUNTEERS FOR STUDY ON STROKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE GRIMM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UCLA Medical Center is seeking 150 volunteers ages 55 to 80 to take part 
in a study on the causes of strokes and memory loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers should be healthy and should not be taking medication for high 
blood pressure or heart ailments. Applicants will receive a free medical 
examination and, if chosen, will be paid $120 to complete the study. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants will visit UCLA six times for a variety of tests and will wear a 
24-hour blood pressure monitor. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 825-6475. DAVE GRIMM 
</P>
</TEXT>
