<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: TORRANCE; NEW PARK NAMED FOR 2 DEVELOPMENT FOES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Torrance officials dedicated a new park recently to a Torrance couple who were 
credited with sparing the area from high-rise development before their deaths 
in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 The park, at 220 Via Riviera in the Hollywood Riviera section of the city, was 
named Mantovani Park in honor of Robert and Juanita Mantovani, who were killed 
in a car accident. 
</P>
<P>
 "Juanita and Bob were always concerned with preserving natural beauty," said 
Marie Watson, Juanita Mantovani's 81-year-old mother. "It's wonderful that they 
are remembered in this beautiful park." JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
