<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: ROLLING HILLS ESTATES; CITY TO OK BUDGET WITH MINOR CHANGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council plans to adopt the city budget for 1994-95 on Tuesday with 
minor changes to capital works programs. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will add $90,000 to the street maintenance budget to fix Rolling 
Hills Road and other residential streets, Finance Director Judy Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city also has allocated $95,000 to create the George F Canyon Nature 
Center, she said. A building at Palos Verdes Drive East and Palos Verdes Drive 
North will be renovated for the center next year. The city has spent $18,000 on 
its design. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith said the city is expecting a $30,000 surplus in its general fund. SUSAN 
WOODWARD 
</P>
