<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; GETTING THE WORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The results of a telephone poll commissioned by World Cup '94 found that 90% 
of those polled in the nine venue cities were able to identify the World Cup as 
a soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 An additional 84% said they were aware that the World Cup is happening in the 
United States. According to the Roper poll, 65% of those surveyed said they 
would like to see a professional soccer league in the United States. JULIE CART 
