<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: SCHOLARSHIPS OFFERED FOR SWIM LESSONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For a splash of fun this summer, youngsters 7 through 17 can take free 
swimming lessons at 13 public pools in the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The Amateur Athletic Foundation is offering scholarships, on a first-come, 
first-served basis, for the two-week swimming sessions.Without the scholarship, 
the sessions cost $12. 
</P>
<P>
 The lessons will include introduction to butterfly and back strokes, plus 
competition strategies and actual racing. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who participate also have the opportunity to qualify for a citywide swim 
meet, the 1994 Summer Swim Festival at the AAF's Rose Bowl Aquatics Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The Valley pools involved in the program are: Fernangeles Pool, Sun Valley; 
Hubert Humphrey Pool and Paxton Pool, Pacoima; Lanark Pool, Canoga Park; Valley 
Plaza Pool, North Hollywood; Granada Hills, Northridge, Reseda, North Hollywood 
and Woodland Hills pools; Sepulveda Pool, Panorama City; Van Nuys/Sherman Oaks 
Pool, Van Nuys, and Verdugo Hills Pool, Tujunga. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
