<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; GOAL IS TO FIND A GOOD KEEPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SIMON BARNES, Times of London 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Behind every great team there is an absolutely appalling goalkeeper. 
</P>
<P>
 I am not sure if we have seen a great team at this World Cup yet, but I am 
quite certain we have seen some dreadful goalkeepers.Why do they pick 'em? 
</P>
<P>
 When you see a goalkeeper give a performance of genuine 24-carat awfulness, 
you have to wonder about his function in the team. It surely can't be that of 
keeping the score down. 
</P>
<P>
 Tying in first place for the worst goalie of the World Cup so far are 
Joseph-Antoine Bell, of Cameroon, and Oscar Cordoba, of Colombia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
