<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; ALL WIGGED OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Out with the Carlos Valderrama bright fright wigs, in with the Alexi Lalas 
look. 
</P>
<P>
 Three youths from Portland, Ore., and one from Garden Grove made that World 
Cup fashion statement before the United States defeated Colombia, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Fletcher, Jeremy Inman and Tom Lathrop of Portland and Micah Fitch of 
Garden Grove were parading around the Rose Bowl on Wednesday wearing bright 
frizzy orange wigs with orange goatees. 
</P>
<P>
 Hundreds of Colombian fans wore the Valderrama wigs. 
</P>
<P>
 "I came to the game last Saturday between Colombia and Romania, and I saw all 
the Valderrama wigs and I just wanted to get behind the United States," Fitch 
said. "Maybe everyone will do it now." 
</P>
<P>
 Said Fletcher: "Alexi is the best. Valderrama? Alexi didn't lose his first 
game like (Valderrama) did." LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
