<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; YOU CAN'T RUN, HIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GRAHAME L. JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the 1986 World Cup, authorities tried to hide the squalor and poverty of 
some sections of Mexico City by enclosing them behind walls brightly decorated 
with folk art.It didn't work. 
</P>
<P>
 In the 1994 World Cup in the United States, authorities in Chicago tried to 
hide the homeless by having the police clear the parks and other areas used by 
squatters. It didn't work, either. The world's press heard about it, and 
Chicago's image got a black eye for its attempted deception. GRAHAME L. JONES 
</P>
