WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; COACH DECLINES HELP WITH NO 
THANKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Criticism in Mexico of Mexico's 1-0 loss to Norway has been intense, both from 
the media and from soccer officials.However, Coach Miguel Mejia Baron remains 
unfazed. 
</P>
<P>
 As he did Sunday, Baron hinted at a lineup change for Friday's game against 
Ireland but declined to name his lineup Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "Whoever plays, it's because it's my decision. I don't care about the media," 
Mejia Baron said. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
