<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES / ANNE MICHAUD: A SUCCULENT PORK TENDERLOIN -- AND ONE BREWSKY, 
PLEASE! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fullerton Hofbrau is offering an interesting twist on the wine dinner this 
Sunday, with dishes prepared to accompany its own micro-brewed beers. 
</P>
<P>
 Chef Horst Voelsing will prepare Scottish smoked salmon with a creamed 
horseradish sauce, served with a summer brew, Hefe-Weizen. Following is a pork 
tenderloin brushed with a beer mustard sauce and green peppercorns, accompanied 
by Earl's Ale. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinner begins with appetizers at 5:30. The price, $38 a person, includes tax 
and tip. Reservations are recommended. 
</P>
<P>
 323 N. State College Blvd. (714) 870-7400. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Andreino DeSantis, who served as a chef for President Reagan's 1986 
inauguration in Washington, will make a five-course Italian dinner for the 
Robert Mondavi Wine & Food Center on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The main course is veal with mushrooms and spring vegetables, served with 
Pinot Noir reserve. Dessert is mixed fruit in Moscato wine and "cappuccino 
Andreino." 
</P>
<P>
 The price is $125, tax and tip included, and dinner begins at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
 1570 Scenic Ave., Costa Mesa. (714) 979-4510. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Bistro will play host to Fetzer Winery on Saturday for a four-course 
dinner accompanied by the vineyard's wines. The menu includes baked eggplant 
with angel hair pasta, served with 1991 Pinot Noir. A bay shrimp Caesar salad 
follows, then pepper steak with asparagus and a 1990 Cabernet Sauvignon. Apple 
cinnamon blintzes with 1989 black Muscat are for dessert. 
</P>
<P>
 The dinner begins with a reception at 7. The price is $65 a person, plus tax 
and tip. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Crystal Court shopping center, 3333 Bear St., Costa Mesa. (714) 
546-6004. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Light drinkers and those who like to sample wines might want to check out the 
Sunset Grille & Bar, where they're serving wine by the half-glass. The "flight 
size" glasses, as the restaurant labels them, are priced at half the cost of 
regular glasses (which generally run $4.75 to $6.25). 
</P>
<P>
 34150 Coast Highway, Dana Point. (714) 661-5220. 
</P>
