<TEXT>
<P>
 James F. Cowan, the former Ventura County superintendent of schools, has been 
selected grand marshal of the 1994 Ventura County Fair parade. 
</P>
<P>
 Cowan, a 62-year-old Ventura resident, was chosen by the fair's board of 
directors for his contributions to the county and his support of youth 
involvement in the fair, said spokeswoman Teri Raley. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm very honored and pleased that they would select me to do that," Cowan 
said Wednesday. "I'm really excited and looking forward to it." 
</P>
<P>
