<P>
JANET EVANS HEADS THE FIELD FOR MISSION VIEJO SWIM MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some of the nation's top swimmers will gather for four days of competition 
starting today at the 25th Swim Meet of Champions at the Marguerite Aquatics 
Complex in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, hosted by the Mission Viejo Nadadores, features Placentia's Janet 
Evans, two-time Olympic medal winner and world-record holder, Olympians Jeff 
Rouse and Angie Wester-Krieg, Stanford breaststroker Kristine Quance and local 
prep sensation Derya Buyukuncu. 
</P>
<P>
 Nadadores Coach Bill Rose said this meet kicks off the summer's senior meets, 
which lead to the World Championships in Rome in September. 
</P>
<P>
 "A lot of top swimmers compete in this meet because it allows them to see 
where they are in their training and how well they'll do against other top 
competitors," Rose said. 
</P>
<P>
 Preliminaries start at 9 a.m with finals scheduled for 5 p.m. today through 
Saturday and 4 p.m. Sunday. Full session tickets are $20 for adults and $5 for 
children. Day passes are $7 for adults and $2 for children. ERIK HAMILTON 
</P>
