<P>
EX-CHIEF LOWERY AGREES WITH JETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kicker Nick Lowery, the third-leading scorer in NFL history, agreed to terms 
on a two-year contract Wednesday with the New York Jets. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms of the deal were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Lowery, 38, played the last 13 seasons with the Kansas City Chiefs after 
starting his NFL career with the New England Patriots in 1978. He has 1,473 
points and is the career field goal accuracy leader at 80%. 
</P>
