<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cap Cities Will Stay in New York: Capital Cities/ABC Inc. said it has struck a 
$26-million agreement with city and state officials to keep the television 
company's headquarters in New York City for the next 15 years.Under the 
agreement, Cap Cities will spend more than $150 million to convert its 
television production facilities to digital and high-definition technologies. 
ABC said it employs 3,700 people in its New York broadcast operations and will 
add 185 workers in the city over the next two years. Similar to deals struck 
between local government and other networks, the ABC deal gives the company $12 
million in sales tax abatements on equipment purchases and $14 million in 
energy savings over 15 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
