<P>
 Bells Ask to Offer Long-Distance Wireless: Seven regional Bells, including 
U.S. West Inc., asked for relief from rules that restrict them from providing 
wireless long-distance services, the company said.In a filing with U.S. 
District Judge Harold Greene, the Baby Bells asked for a waiver to the 1982 
consent decree that broke up AT&T and created the Bells but restricted them 
from manufacturing and providing long-distance services. The request follows a 
recommendation last week by the Justice Department that the regional companies 
be allowed to provide wireless long-distance services. However, that ruling 
came with a number of restrictions, which the Bells say will hurt them in 
competing with other wireless services companies. 
