<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vans Inc.: The maker of athletic shoes said Wednesday that it has appointed 
its controller, Karen J. Ratcliff, to vice president and chief financial 
officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Ratcliff, 41, will replace Winston E. Hickman, who is leaving the Orange-based 
company July 31 to pursue other business interests. He said he did not know 
what he would do next. 
</P>
<P>
 Ratcliff joined Vans as controller in early 1991. She was acting chief 
financial officer from February to September, 1992. Before joining Vans, 
Ratcliff worked as assistant chief accountant for the Securities and Exchange 
Commission's division of corporation finance. She also held numerous positions 
at accounting firm KPMG Peat Marwick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
