<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Winning Builders: Irvine Co. has selected several firms to build single-family 
homes in the company's Northwood 5 project near Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Twelve builders were vying for the opportunity, but the developer tapped five 
with which to negotiate exclusively. The winners: Kaufman & Broad in Los 
Angeles, Costain Homes in Newport Beach, Standard Pacific Corp. in Costa Mesa, 
Taylor Woodrow Homes California Ltd. in Laguna Hills and Pardee Construction of 
Los Angeles.  
</P>
<P>
 "We were very pleased to have such depth and breadth of builder interest in 
this project, which suggests improving economic conditions and strong 
confidence about this location," which is in an unincorporated area of Orange 
County near Jeffrey Road, said Larry Thomas, spokesman for Irvine Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
