<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOINGS ON; FILM SERIES OPENING AT UC SANTA BARBARA; AS SUMMER OFFERINGS ARE 
ANNOUNCED, THE ARTS & LECTURES STAFF IS LINING UP VARIED MUSIC, DANCE AND 
DRAMATIC PERFORMANCES FOR FALL. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEO SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 School may be out, but UC Santa Barbara's Arts & Lectures department seems to 
be keeping busy, with the kick-off to a film series at Campbell Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 Topping the schedule are two highly acclaimed releases from last year. "In the 
Name of the Father" stars Daniel Day-Lewis and Emma Thompson, and will be shown 
tonight, and the Vietnamese movie "The Scent of Green Papaya" will be shown 
Sunday. Both movies will begin at 7 p.m. General admission is $5. Call 893-3535 
for information. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the Arts & Lectures staff is preparing for the fall's performance 
schedule. A sampling of the 1993-94 lineup: the National Theater of the Deaf, 
the Chamber Music Society of Lincoln Center, the Gyuto Monks Tibetan Tantric 
Choir, Mariachi Los Camperos de Nati Cano, the Gay Men's Chorus of Los Angeles, 
the Brave Old World klezmer band and the Margaret Jenkins Dance Company. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Local bluegrass favorites the Cache Valley Drifters will take the stage Friday 
night in the next installment of the "Presidio Unplugged" series at the Santa 
Barbara Presidio Chapel. Show time is 8 p.m. Admission is $6 (advance), $7 (at 
the door). Call 965-0093. The Presidio is at 129 E. Canon Perdido St. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Barbara Historical Arms Assn. Inc. is holding its 34th annual Summer 
Arms and Blades Show on Saturday and Sunday at the Earl Warren Showgrounds. In 
the past, exhibited items have dated back to the 1600s. Displays have included 
British Sea Service pistols, Civil War and Revolutionary War items, and weapons 
used at the Alamo. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours are 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday and 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Sunday. Admission is 
$5 (adults), $3 (children 12 and younger) and $1 (those 62 and older). Call 
687-0766 for information. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Local composer Vernon Martin will pay tribute to the life and work of Andrea 
Lang at SOhO on Monday, the fourth anniversary of the artist's death in the 
Santa Barbara Painted Cave fire. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin and his Universal Unity Rhythm, Sound and Motion group will perform the 
multimedia piece, "For Andrea Lang: Music From the Painted Cave." They will be 
joined by the Ana Galindo Flamenco Troupe. 
</P>
<P>
 The concert will begin at 8 p.m., with a 10 p.m. show to be added if demand 
for tickets warrants it. Admission, on a sliding scale, is $10 to $20. SOhO is 
at 1221 State St., Suite 205 (on the second level of Victoria Court). For 
information, call the Contemporary Arts Forum at 966-5373. Lang's work is on 
exhibit at CAF through Aug. 6. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 World-renowned opera stars Thomas Hampson and Frederica von Stade will perform 
with the Santa Barbara Symphony Orchestra on Tuesday at Santa Barbara's 
Arlington Theatre. 
</P>
<P>
 Hampson and von Stade have performed with New York's Metropolitan Opera, and 
have played classic opera roles in premier opera houses throughout Europe. This 
will be their first time on stage together. 
</P>
<P>
 The evening's program will include arias from Mozart's "Don Giovanni" and "The 
Marriage of Figaro," Rossini's "Barber of Seville," Verdi's "Don Carlo" and 
Bizet's "Carmen." Hampson and von Stade will also perform a selection of 
Broadway tunes from "Carousel" and "Showboat." The performance will begin at 8 
p.m. Tickets are $35, $30 and $25. Call 963-4408. The Arlington is at 1317 
State St. 
</P>
