<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; MARINES GET VOICE ON BASE REUSE PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TAMMERLIN DRUMMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The El Toro Reuse Planning Authority voted Wednesday to include a Marine 
ex-officio member on the authority's board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. Marine Col. Jim Ritchie was appointed a non-voting member representing 
the base commander, Gen. Drax Williams.Ritchie will serve as an adviser to the 
authority's voting members. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're bringing him in to answer questions that might come up since he has 
been involved at the Marine headquarters level," said Orange County Supervisor 
Thomas F. Riley, who chairs the planning authority. "We wanted somebody with 
the extra up-to-date information that would help us move forward." 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the board also voted to delay authorizing an environmental study 
until a specific reuse plan for the base has been decided. 
</P>
<P>
 "It would have cost us twice the amount of money to do another environmental 
study," Riley said. "We decided that it would be least costly to do it the way 
we're doing it." TAMMERLIN DRUMMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
