<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; COUNCIL RESTRICTS GARAGE-SALE DAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has given final approval to an ordinance that allows garage 
sales only on the first weekend in March, June, September and December. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance was drafted in an effort to crack down on illegal businesses and 
clean up the city's neighborhoods, where residents use frequent yard sales as 
both a means of income and an affordable shopping alternative to secondhand 
stores. 
</P>
<P>
 The first city-sanctioned garage sale weekend will be in September, according 
to code enforcement officials, who will begin to cite violators in August. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said they will spend the next month getting the word out to 
residents via water bills and the media about the new law. 
</P>
<P>
 Once the ordinance takes effect, anyone holding a garage sale outside the four 
sanctioned weekends risks a fine and will have the goods confiscated, pending a 
hearing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
