<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; UCI PROFESSOR WINS WILSON FELLOWSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brook Thomas, an English professor at UC Irvine, is one of 32 scholars chosen 
as a Woodrow Wilson fellow for the upcoming academic year. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas and the other 31 academics were chosen from among 819 applicants from 
82 countries.They will spend a year at the Woodrow Wilson International Center 
for Scholars in Washington. Thomas will pursue research in American literary 
realism. 
</P>
<P>
 Created in 1968 as the nation's official memorial to its 28th President, the 
Wilson center houses an annual residential fellowship program, plays host to 
conferences on a range of public policy issues and publishes various 
periodicals and books. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas graduated from Stanford University in 1970 and received her Ph.D. from 
UC Santa Barbara five years later. 
</P>
<P>
 She taught at universities in Germany, Hawaii and Massachusetts before joining 
the faculty at Irvine in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 She has authored three books of literary criticism.JODI WILGOREN 
</P>
</TEXT>
