<P>
SKIP LOADER HITS FIRETRUCK; 1 HURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Orange County Fire Department engine about to take part in a traffic 
accident rescue drill was crushed Wednesday evening by a 45,000-pound skip 
loader that careened across Los Alisos Boulevard and smashed into the parked 
firetruck. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the skip loader escaped injuries and the driver of the fire 
engine suffered only bruises to one arm, but the $200,000 firetruck may have 
been destroyed, Fire Department spokeswoman Emmy Day said. 
</P>
<P>
 Day said the accident is still under investigation, but officials speculate 
that a mechanical problem may have caused the skip loader to go out of control. 
</P>
