<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOOTING VICTIM FOUND IN CAR IDENTIFIED BY POLICE AS 23-YEAR-OLD L.A. WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The body of a woman who had been shot "multiple times" and left in the back 
seat of a parked car has been identified as that of 23-year-old Sherri 
Cabaccang of Los Angeles, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cabaccang's late-model Ford Mustang had been parked in a commercial lot near 
Westmont Drive and Euclid Street at least since Sunday, Sgt. Steve Rodig 
said.Someone finally notified police about the car on Tuesday and the body was 
discovered. 
</P>
<P>
 "The body was in the back seat, out of view," Rodig said. "We believe she was 
shot at the same location where the car was found. It is unknown how long she 
had been inside of the vehicle." 
</P>
<P>
 Rodig said police have no suspects and have not established a motive. 
</P>
<P>
 "We still have a lot of work to do on this case," Rodig said. "We don't know 
much" about Cabaccang, who lived in Los Angeles' Harbor City section. "We are 
still contacting family members and trying to determine a motive for why this 
may have happened." 
</P>
