<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WOODLAND HILLS; WALKATHON TO BENEFIT PIERCE COLLEGE FARM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A walkathon to raise money for the reseeding of Pierce College's alfalfa 
pastures is scheduled July 4 at the college. 
</P>
<P>
 The event at 8:30 a.m. also will raise funds for the revitalization of 
Pierce's farm in general.Participants will meet at the school's DeSoto Avenue 
entrance. A three-hour limit has been placed on 2K and 5K stretches, allowing 
for all levels of walkers and runners. 
</P>
<P>
 A minimum donation will be charged participants. The walkathon will kick off a 
day of activities at Pierce. Also planned are an open swimming program and a 
concert on the lawn. 
</P>
<P>
 At 5:30 p.m., entertainment that includes an Independence Day fireworks 
display sponsored by the Woodland Hills Chamber of Commerce will begin. MAKI 
BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
