<P>
 In a move that surprised Burroughs High athletic officials, quarterback Scott 
Boldvich has transferred to Foothill League rival Hart. Boldvich passed for 840 
yards and one touchdown as a junior last season as Burroughs finished 5-6 and 
reached the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 In March, he supported Pat Blackburn as a replacement for Coach Gary Bernardi, 
now an assistant at UCLA. Burroughs hired Robert dos Remedios. Baseball 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Hankins of Simi Valley High was two for three and scored a run Wednesday 
as California defeated Oklahoma, 7-2, in the Sunbelt Seniors Baseball Classic 
in Edmond, Okla. 
</P>
<P>
 Hankins had four hits and drove in two runs in California's 18-1 victory 
Tuesday over Maryland as Brian Bowles of Peninsula and Brian Scott of San Diego 
Ramona combined for a no-hitter. 
